/-- The class number of a number field is `1` iff the ring of integers is a PID. -/
theorem class_number_eq_one_iff : class_number K = 1 ↔ is_principal_ideal_ring (ring_of_integers K) :=
  card_class_group_eq_one_iff
#align class_number_eq_one_iff class_number_eq_one_iff
class_number_eq:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr →+* » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `exprℚ -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `exprℚ -/
theorem class_number_eq : number_field.class_number (exprℚ) = 1 :=
  class_number_eq_one_iff.mpr <| by
    convert
      is_principal_ideal_ring.of_surjective (rat.ring_of_integers_equiv.symm : «expr →+* » ℤ (ring_of_integers (exprℚ)))
        rat.ring_of_integers_equiv.symm.surjective
#align class_number_eq class_number_eq
